WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:04.046
I made a decision
to get sober in order
to be the best father

00:04.046 --> 00:05.297
I could be for Theo,
and I am making the decision

00:05.297 --> 00:07.341
to be the best father
I can be for Charlie.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.842
And the only way
is to tell the truth.

00:08.842 --> 00:10.385
Delilah:
<i>Don't we all have secrets?</i>

00:10.385 --> 00:12.095
I almost lost you
eight months ago.

00:12.095 --> 00:14.389
But today,
you were strong, unafraid.

00:14.389 --> 00:16.767
I'm saying
I want to adopt a baby.

00:16.767 --> 00:18.602
<i>Things we hide</i>
<i>to protect each other...</i>

00:18.602 --> 00:19.895
About the night Chad died.

00:19.895 --> 00:21.396
Eric has
your brother's heart.

00:21.396 --> 00:23.398
<i>...to protect ourselves...</i>
School musical?

00:23.398 --> 00:24.816
You guys are doing
"Grease"?

00:24.816 --> 00:26.276
Danny: Elliot
got called back, too.

00:26.276 --> 00:28.070
Your ex Elliot?
<i>Sometimes...</i>

00:28.070 --> 00:30.697
Gary:
Nine months ago, I sat here
as a breast cancer survivor.

00:30.697 --> 00:33.450
Today, I'm in love
with a breast cancer survivor.

00:33.450 --> 00:34.993
<i>...the truth...</i>
You keep saying

00:34.993 --> 00:36.828
you need to know
who you are without cancer.

00:36.828 --> 00:39.289
Maybe I need to figure out
who I am without <i>you.</i>

00:39.289 --> 00:40.541
<i>...just hurts too much.</i>

00:40.541 --> 00:41.917
Eric:
I'm helping her move right now.

00:41.917 --> 00:44.211
I'm gonna tell her.
Now is not the right time.

00:44.211 --> 00:46.630
<i>It makes you wonder ‐‐</i>
<i>is honesty...</i>

00:46.630 --> 00:47.756
Here's the form
you wanted.

00:47.756 --> 00:49.174
It says
that you're Charlie's father.

00:49.174 --> 00:50.592
<i>...really the best policy?</i>

00:50.592 --> 00:52.010
There's something
we need to talk about.

00:53.679 --> 00:55.764
You spoke at his funeral!

00:57.599 --> 00:59.142
[ Grunts ]

01:01.603 --> 01:06.733
♪♪

01:06.733 --> 01:09.861
[ Sniffling ]

01:09.861 --> 01:14.408
♪♪

01:14.408 --> 01:16.159
I trusted you!

01:18.412 --> 01:21.164
I understand
that you're angry.

01:21.164 --> 01:23.792
Believe me, I get it.

01:23.792 --> 01:29.464
♪♪

01:29.464 --> 01:31.383
[ Breathing shakily ]

01:31.383 --> 01:33.343
[ Vehicle approaches ]

01:35.887 --> 01:36.930
[ Car door closes ]

01:36.930 --> 01:40.642
♪♪

01:40.642 --> 01:42.060
Wait. Wait.

01:42.060 --> 01:44.187
Sophie, please.
Can we just ‐‐

01:44.187 --> 01:45.856
Sophie,
I want to talk to you.

01:48.900 --> 01:50.819
You killed Dad.

01:50.819 --> 01:57.617
♪♪

01:57.617 --> 01:58.785
[ Door slams ]

01:58.785 --> 02:04.791
♪♪

02:18.221 --> 02:21.350
[ Charlie crying ]

02:21.350 --> 02:23.852
It's okay, sweetie.
You're just ‐‐

02:23.852 --> 02:25.729
You're just getting
your first tooth.

02:25.729 --> 02:27.022
Only 19 more to go.

02:27.022 --> 02:28.273
Katherine: Found it!

02:28.273 --> 02:30.317
Can't open it,
but I found it.

02:30.317 --> 02:31.943
[ Grunts ]

02:31.943 --> 02:33.403
[ Crying continues ]

02:33.403 --> 02:35.322
Maybe we should check with
Delilah and make sure she's okay

02:35.322 --> 02:37.616
with us giving Charlie
acetaminophen.

02:37.616 --> 02:39.576
Of course.

02:39.576 --> 02:41.495
And, Eddie,
you're her dad.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.413
<i>You can make those decisions</i>
<i>for her, too.</i>

02:43.413 --> 02:45.248
Thanks, D.
Sorry if we woke you.

02:45.248 --> 02:46.416
<i>No, you didn't.</i>

02:46.416 --> 02:48.752
I'm up waiting for Sophie.
She's late again.

02:48.752 --> 02:49.961
[ Vehicle approaches ]

02:49.961 --> 02:51.004
Oh. She's home.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.631
[ Charlie fusses ]

02:52.631 --> 02:53.632
Good luck.

02:53.632 --> 02:54.841
<i>You too.</i>

02:54.841 --> 02:56.093
Okay, bye.

02:56.093 --> 02:57.469
<i>Bye.</i>
[ Cellphone beeps ]

02:57.469 --> 02:58.887
Well, hello.

02:58.887 --> 03:00.555
It's an hour
past your curfew.

03:00.555 --> 03:03.600
Uh, actually, it's an hour
and nine minutes past my curfew.

03:03.600 --> 03:05.519
Sophie!

03:05.519 --> 03:07.312
Oh. I'm sorry.

03:07.312 --> 03:09.356
I didn't realize we lived
in a house with rules.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.025
You know what?
You're grounded.
Awesome.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.402
Means I don't have to
work at the restaurant.

03:13.402 --> 03:15.862
Yes, you do!
You're paying for those guitars.

03:15.862 --> 03:19.533
♪♪

03:19.533 --> 03:20.867
[ Sighs ]

03:20.867 --> 03:27.541
♪♪

03:27.541 --> 03:28.875
[ Door opens ]

03:30.502 --> 03:31.837
Oh, no.

03:31.837 --> 03:33.296
Elise!

03:33.296 --> 03:35.465
I said I wanted
the blue pens that click!

03:35.465 --> 03:37.342
These ones with the caps
just slow me down!

03:39.719 --> 03:40.971
Oh, actually,
those are pretty good.

03:40.971 --> 03:42.097
Gary.
[ Door closes ]

03:42.097 --> 03:43.098
How are you?

03:43.098 --> 03:44.891
I don't know, Doc.
That's why I'm here.

03:44.891 --> 03:46.768
Anything on that chart
you want to share with me?

03:46.768 --> 03:49.479
You can tell me.
You <i>should</i> tell me.

03:49.479 --> 03:51.106
Just tell me.

03:51.106 --> 03:52.524
We did a full panel.

03:54.985 --> 03:56.111
Everything
came back negative.

03:56.111 --> 03:58.238
Oh‐ho‐ho! Thank God!

03:58.238 --> 03:59.656
[ Inhales sharply ]

03:59.656 --> 04:01.825
So, my penis
isn't gonna fall off?

04:01.825 --> 04:03.034
Not today, no.

04:03.034 --> 04:05.036
Uh, but, Gary,

04:05.036 --> 04:07.831
even for me, you stripped down
when you didn't need to.

04:07.831 --> 04:09.958
If you're gonna be
this sexually active, you ‐‐

04:09.958 --> 04:10.959
you need to be careful.

04:10.959 --> 04:12.002
I'm <i>always</i> careful.

04:13.128 --> 04:14.921
I'm <i>usually</i> careful.
Mm...

04:14.921 --> 04:16.173
I always try
to be careful.

04:16.173 --> 04:18.425
Hey, speaking of,
do me a solid.

04:18.425 --> 04:20.051
Show my all‐clear chart
to your nurse, would you?

04:20.051 --> 04:21.261
We were flirting
in the waiting room.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.971
She kinda had
a wait‐and‐see attitude.

04:24.014 --> 04:25.348
Be good, Gary.
You too, man.

04:25.348 --> 04:26.141
Alright.

04:27.642 --> 04:28.643
[ Door closes ]

04:28.643 --> 04:29.811
[ Claps hands ]

04:29.811 --> 04:31.104
Here you go, sweetie.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.189
Tastes like...

04:32.189 --> 04:33.273
frozen wash cloth.

04:33.273 --> 04:34.816
She does not want it.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.067
Who <i>would?</i>

04:36.067 --> 04:38.403
Try this. It says
it's perfect for teething.

04:38.403 --> 04:39.654
Oh.

04:39.654 --> 04:41.031
Where'd you get that?

04:41.031 --> 04:43.784
It was in the package
of baby stuff from Aunt Lindsay.

04:43.784 --> 04:45.452
Aunt Lindsay?

04:45.452 --> 04:47.329
Yeah, I found it
on the front steps.

04:47.329 --> 04:49.039
I thought it was
my new sleep mask.

04:52.167 --> 04:54.377
That was really...
nice of her.

04:54.377 --> 04:57.255
Yeah, and her note said
she can't wait to meet the baby.

04:57.255 --> 04:59.007
She hasn't even met <i>me.</i>

04:59.007 --> 05:01.384
She wants to,
but she's just really busy.

05:01.384 --> 05:04.012
But you're her brother.
Doesn't she want to see <i>you?</i>

05:04.012 --> 05:05.889
[ Charlie coos ]
It's just...

05:05.889 --> 05:08.725
she...travels a lot, T.

05:08.725 --> 05:10.727
Well, she should
travel <i>here.</i>

05:13.104 --> 05:14.231
[ Charlie coos ]

05:17.818 --> 05:20.612
Sophie, come on!
Breakfast is on the table!

05:20.612 --> 05:22.239
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Croissants!

05:22.239 --> 05:24.032
She says
she's not hungry.
What?

05:24.032 --> 05:26.535
I don't care
if you're not hungry!

05:26.535 --> 05:27.994
You know what?
Give me that.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

05:27.994 --> 05:29.162
Two can play this game.

05:31.206 --> 05:32.624
Why's she asking you
about a kiss?

05:32.624 --> 05:33.875
Um...

05:33.875 --> 05:36.044
she's...talking
about "Grease."

05:36.044 --> 05:38.964
She wants to know if Sandy and I
kissed in rehearsal yet.

05:38.964 --> 05:40.799
Have you?
No.

05:40.799 --> 05:43.593
But you have to
for the show tonight, right?

05:43.593 --> 05:44.678
You nervous?

05:44.678 --> 05:46.972
No. It's just
a stupid part of the play.

05:46.972 --> 05:49.224
I'm not nervous.
People kiss.

05:49.224 --> 05:50.016
Right.

05:51.601 --> 05:54.229
How about Elliot? You never
talk about him anymore.

05:54.229 --> 05:56.147
Is he good as Kenickie?

05:56.147 --> 05:57.440
He's okay.

05:57.440 --> 05:58.608
He mostly ignores me.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.443
Maybe that's because
he actually likes you

06:00.443 --> 06:02.904
[Whispering] and he doesn't
want anyone to know.

06:02.904 --> 06:06.157
Or maybe
he just <i>doesn't</i> like me.

06:06.157 --> 06:07.033
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:10.120 --> 06:12.122
Sophie's not coming
tonight.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.290
What?

06:13.290 --> 06:15.125
Because <i>I'm</i> go‐‐
N‐‐ That ‐‐

06:15.125 --> 06:16.376
She will be there.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.295
Please don't do anything.

06:18.295 --> 06:20.255
She can see it tomorrow.

06:20.255 --> 06:21.715
I don't want
to make things worse.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.758
[ Footsteps ]
It is your opening night,
and she will ‐‐

06:23.758 --> 06:25.218
[ Door closes ]

06:25.218 --> 06:26.511
What ‐‐
Did she just leave?
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:26.511 --> 06:27.637
She's waiting for me
in the car.

06:29.180 --> 06:31.224
Hey, Mom,
it took a while

06:31.224 --> 06:33.101
before <i>you</i> could talk
about stuff, too.

06:33.101 --> 06:35.729
Maybe she just needs
more time.

06:35.729 --> 06:37.147
[ Chuckles lightly ]

06:37.147 --> 06:38.148
Maybe.

06:38.148 --> 06:39.482
[ Both smooch ]

06:39.482 --> 06:40.483
[ Chuckles ]

06:42.319 --> 06:44.487
Maggie and Gary are coming,
aren't they?

06:44.487 --> 06:45.822
Yeah, yeah.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.324
Of course.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.992
But not together?

06:48.992 --> 06:50.869
No.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.662
I still don't get it.

06:52.662 --> 06:54.497
I know. Me either.

06:55.957 --> 06:57.417
Hey, Danny.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.711
You only
make things better.

06:59.711 --> 07:01.046
[ Chuckles softly ]

07:02.631 --> 07:05.425
Uh‐oh, Brandon.

07:05.425 --> 07:07.761
Aaaaaaa...ha!

07:07.761 --> 07:08.845
I got your nose!

07:08.845 --> 07:10.055
I got your nose!

07:10.055 --> 07:11.806
[ Brandon whimpers ]

07:11.806 --> 07:13.183
Oh.
Babe.

07:13.183 --> 07:14.643
N‐No, no, no. Hey.
Mommy!

07:14.643 --> 07:16.686
Mommy's here.
She's right here.

07:16.686 --> 07:18.730
Hey, Brandon, I‐I don't
really have your nose.
It's just my thumb.

07:18.730 --> 07:20.357
Mommy! [ Crying ]

07:20.357 --> 07:22.442
What happened?
Gloria: I'm right here.
Come here. Co‐‐ Come on.

07:22.442 --> 07:25.862
I am so sorry
that I had to bring him.

07:25.862 --> 07:28.365
These house visits
book up so fast.

07:28.365 --> 07:31.076
And my ex promised
<i>he'd</i> take him.

07:31.076 --> 07:33.495
Brandon promises
a lot of things.

07:33.495 --> 07:35.914
Oh, yeah.
They have the same name.

07:35.914 --> 07:37.165
It just keeps on giving.

07:37.165 --> 07:39.584
No problem.
We love kids.

07:39.584 --> 07:41.920
Especially kids with noses.
Which you have! [ Chuckles ]

07:41.920 --> 07:44.339
Drop it.
I can't seem to.

07:44.339 --> 07:47.550
Okay. Well, let's get back
to getting <i>you</i> guys a kid.

07:47.550 --> 07:49.469
You want to show me
the rest of the house?

07:49.469 --> 07:51.388
Yes. Want to show us
the rest of the house?
Yes.

07:51.388 --> 07:53.973
He really doesn't want to.
I want you to be good.
Hear me?

07:53.973 --> 07:55.266
Okay.

07:55.266 --> 07:57.060
Eddie: Alright, T.
I e‐mailed them.

07:57.060 --> 07:59.479
They're gonna refund us
the two‐day shipping
on the sleep mask.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.481
Now go get dressed!
[ Giggling ]
Okay! Okay.

08:03.775 --> 08:05.902
So, how did she know
you had a baby?

08:07.112 --> 08:08.321
Have you been
in touch with her?

08:08.321 --> 08:11.366
I s‐‐ sent her
the birth announcement.

08:11.366 --> 08:14.369
The thing is,
Theo has a sister now,

08:14.369 --> 08:16.454
and it reminded me
of mine.

08:16.454 --> 08:19.416
Eddie, she <i>cannot</i> be
back in our life.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.000
Oh, I know.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.919
But, I mean,
she's my sister.

08:22.919 --> 08:24.879
Yeah, she was also
your first drinking buddy,

08:24.879 --> 08:28.091
and you guys enabled each other
for half your life.

08:28.091 --> 08:29.759
I'm just trying
to protect you.

08:29.759 --> 08:31.386
<i>And</i> Theo.

08:31.386 --> 08:34.097
And now he has
all these questions.

08:34.097 --> 08:35.348
What are we gonna tell him?

08:35.348 --> 08:37.934
Well, if I've learned anything
this past year ‐‐

08:37.934 --> 08:40.103
from you ‐‐

08:40.103 --> 08:42.063
it's how important it is
to be honest.

08:44.399 --> 08:46.151
I think we need to tell him
the truth about her.

08:48.945 --> 08:50.530
[ Espresso machine hissing ]

08:50.530 --> 08:51.948
You know what?

08:51.948 --> 08:54.075
Let's skip the coffee
and...

08:54.075 --> 08:55.577
just have breakfast in bed.

08:58.038 --> 09:01.291
I am <i>not</i> putting that
on my dating profile.

09:01.291 --> 09:04.210
And please tell me
that is not on <i>yours.</i>

09:04.210 --> 09:07.547
No, my brand is more
"cuddly but hard to get,"

09:07.547 --> 09:09.674
a mystery
wrapped in a cardigan.

09:09.674 --> 09:11.634
Yeah? How many dates
have you been on?

09:11.634 --> 09:13.386
[ Inhales sharply ]
Oof. [ Flaps lips ]

09:13.386 --> 09:15.346
Well, let me see.
Uh, there was the one with ‐‐

09:15.346 --> 09:16.347
None. Not one.

09:16.347 --> 09:18.558
[ Both laugh ]

09:18.558 --> 09:20.935
It's just too soon
for me to jump back into

09:20.935 --> 09:23.021
the cesspool
that is dating in Boston.

09:23.021 --> 09:25.273
You don't think
Gary's on one of these things?

09:25.273 --> 09:28.026
I haven't...seen him
since we broke up.

09:28.026 --> 09:29.652
And of course he is.

09:29.652 --> 09:31.446
[ Chuckles lightly ]

09:31.446 --> 09:33.114
[ Sighs ] It's just ‐‐
It's not easy

09:33.114 --> 09:36.284
to be physically vulnerable
to somebody new.

09:36.284 --> 09:38.369
I mean, <i>you</i> know.
You get it.

09:38.369 --> 09:40.163
You have a scar that's
probably bigger than mine.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.291
Why don't you, uh,

09:43.291 --> 09:46.169
put that kind of honesty
into your profile?

09:46.169 --> 09:48.546
Yeah,
so something like, uh...

09:48.546 --> 09:51.341
"Single, emotionally,
and physically scarred woman

09:51.341 --> 09:53.676
seeks similar man
for unhealthy relationship"?

09:53.676 --> 09:56.179
Uhp. And also don't forget
you're lactose‐intolerant.

09:56.179 --> 09:57.055
Ah.

09:57.055 --> 09:59.057
Maybe <i>you</i> two should date.

09:59.057 --> 10:00.391
Us?
What?

10:00.391 --> 10:01.726
No.
No. [ Chuckles ]

10:01.726 --> 10:03.394
He's got my brother's heart.
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

10:03.394 --> 10:05.063
Oh, he's dating your brother?
That's sweet.

10:05.063 --> 10:05.814
No.

10:05.814 --> 10:07.482
No, he <i>has</i> his heart.

10:07.482 --> 10:08.817
Um...
Transplant.

10:08.817 --> 10:09.818
You know...

10:09.818 --> 10:11.152
Uh‐huh.

10:11.152 --> 10:12.695
I'll just...get the check.

10:12.695 --> 10:14.614
Uh, "checks." [ Chuckles ]
'Cause we're not together.

10:14.614 --> 10:15.615
Oh. Yeah.

10:15.615 --> 10:16.825
Right.

10:16.825 --> 10:17.992
[ Clears throat ]

10:17.992 --> 10:19.702
[ Laughing ]
Thought we were dating.

10:19.702 --> 10:21.246
[ Both laugh ]

10:21.246 --> 10:23.248
That is crazy.
It's so crazy.

10:23.248 --> 10:24.958
[ Both laugh ]

10:26.209 --> 10:27.752
[ Inhales deeply ]
I'm just gonna sign up.

10:27.752 --> 10:29.587
Yeah, I ‐‐ That's what I said.
You should totally sign up.

10:29.587 --> 10:30.713
Signing.

10:30.713 --> 10:31.881
Boop, boop, boop.

10:35.093 --> 10:38.388
You know what? For the record,
I was not worried, okay?

10:38.388 --> 10:40.348
That woman called <i>me</i>
in a panic.

10:40.348 --> 10:42.392
♪ There was a friend
who had a scare ♪

10:42.392 --> 10:44.644
♪ And Gary was his name‐o ♪

10:44.644 --> 10:46.688
♪ G‐A‐R‐R‐Y ♪
[ Laughs ]

10:46.688 --> 10:48.022
You know
my name has one "R."

10:48.022 --> 10:50.024
Y‐Y‐Yeah, I know, but it
wouldn't work rhythmically.

10:50.024 --> 10:52.485
Wait, your STD joke is
referencing a children's song?

10:52.485 --> 10:54.195
Yeah,
the social worker's here.

10:54.195 --> 10:55.780
Oh, yeah.
How's that going?

10:55.780 --> 10:57.657
Great, unless she's heard
any of this conversation.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.701
Well, I gotta
get to Danny's school, dude.

10:59.701 --> 11:00.952
Curtain's in 12 hours.

11:00.952 --> 11:02.745
We haven't finished
painting the sets.

11:02.745 --> 11:03.997
<i>They're not done?</i>

11:03.997 --> 11:05.748
Yeah, it's a long story.

11:05.748 --> 11:07.542
Speaking of <i>long</i> stories ‐‐

11:07.542 --> 11:08.501
<i>Would you stop it?!</i>

11:08.501 --> 11:10.336
Wait.

11:10.336 --> 11:12.213
That one actually
sounds like a complime‐‐

11:12.213 --> 11:14.174
Hey!

11:14.174 --> 11:16.593
It's a stop sign!
It means "Stop"!

11:17.969 --> 11:19.721
Hell is wrong with people?

11:19.721 --> 11:21.598
You know what you would
test positive for?

11:21.598 --> 11:23.141
Anger.

11:23.141 --> 11:24.893
You're gonna get hurt,
you keep acting like this.

11:24.893 --> 11:26.394
Thank you for the concern.

11:26.394 --> 11:28.563
Seriously,
I am worried about you.

11:28.563 --> 11:30.690
Okay, I don't know about
the choices you're making, bro.

11:30.690 --> 11:31.858
<i>First Maggie ‐‐</i>

11:31.858 --> 11:34.527
Well, I didn't choose that.
<i>She</i> did.

11:34.527 --> 11:36.362
I gotta go.
I'm late, man.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

11:36.362 --> 11:46.080
♪♪

11:52.921 --> 11:54.881
[ Sighs ]

12:09.812 --> 12:15.360
♪♪

12:15.360 --> 12:20.865
♪♪

12:20.865 --> 12:23.785
[ Girls laughing ]

12:23.785 --> 12:25.912
Miles: Hey, do you think
they're talking about <i>us?</i>

12:25.912 --> 12:27.413
Probably.

12:27.413 --> 12:29.499
So, Dixon,
tonight's the night.

12:29.499 --> 12:31.209
Are you gonna use tongue
when you kiss her?

12:31.209 --> 12:33.920
I'll...see how it goes.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.256
What about you, Elliot?
I think Haley likes you.

12:36.256 --> 12:37.966
I bet you can't wait
to kiss her.

12:37.966 --> 12:39.175
Totally. [ Chuckles ]

12:40.260 --> 12:42.136
[ School bell rings ]

12:42.136 --> 12:49.143
♪♪

12:49.143 --> 12:50.645
No, feel better.

12:50.645 --> 12:52.939
Of course.
I understand.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.232
Okay. Bye.

12:55.483 --> 12:56.526
Hey!

12:56.526 --> 12:57.902
Hi!

12:57.902 --> 12:59.654
Hi, little munchkin!

12:59.654 --> 13:01.155
Ate like a champ.

13:01.155 --> 13:03.533
Aww.
And slept
six hours straight.

13:03.533 --> 13:05.952
[ Chuckling ] Yes!

13:05.952 --> 13:07.954
The sleep training
is working!

13:07.954 --> 13:09.956
My sitter just canceled.

13:09.956 --> 13:11.749
<i>I</i> can watch Charlie.

13:11.749 --> 13:14.961
No, you're going to the show.
Danny wants everyone there.

13:14.961 --> 13:17.839
And now it looks like
<i>you're</i> gonna go, too, right?

13:17.839 --> 13:20.717
[ Chuckling ] At least <i>one</i>
of his sisters will be there.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.260
Sophie's not coming?

13:22.260 --> 13:24.804
Sophie's not doing
a lot of things she should.

13:24.804 --> 13:26.347
And she still
won't go to therapy.

13:28.599 --> 13:30.435
I'm sorry, Delilah.

13:30.435 --> 13:32.437
I can't help but feel
partially responsible ‐‐

13:32.437 --> 13:34.939
You ‐‐ You didn't know
this was gonna happen.

13:36.816 --> 13:38.026
But <i>you</i> did.

13:42.071 --> 13:45.450
Your place looks great.

13:45.450 --> 13:48.953
And thank you
for making Brandon a snack.

13:48.953 --> 13:51.122
He's gonna always want his
grilled cheese made like that.

13:51.122 --> 13:52.915
Say "Thank you."
Thank you.

13:52.915 --> 13:54.417
Well, yeah,
she's the best.

13:54.417 --> 13:56.711
<i>We're</i> the best.
W‐We're a team.

13:56.711 --> 13:59.297
Not that you can't do it alone.
Single mothers are amazing.

13:59.297 --> 14:01.090
I mean, my mom was...

14:01.090 --> 14:02.508
not a single mom.

14:02.508 --> 14:04.927
But...she could've been.

14:04.927 --> 14:06.679
Regina: Okay. I'm sorry.
[ Chuckles ]

14:06.679 --> 14:09.599
He just really wants this.

14:09.599 --> 14:10.767
And so do I.

14:10.767 --> 14:12.101
Okay, well, great.

14:12.101 --> 14:13.978
I got all your forms
this morning.

14:13.978 --> 14:15.605
The marriage license,
birth certificate,

14:15.605 --> 14:18.024
I got the tax returns,
I got your medical history ‐‐

14:18.024 --> 14:19.692
Medical histories?

14:19.692 --> 14:21.194
Uh, yeah. I...
You got
the medical histories?

14:21.194 --> 14:22.653
I filled them out
this morning.

14:22.653 --> 14:23.946
Yeah, so we are
all set.

14:23.946 --> 14:25.490
I'll be in touch.

14:25.490 --> 14:26.866
It looks good for you guys.

14:26.866 --> 14:28.284
Say "Bye‐bye."
Bye.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.619
Bye. [ Chuckles ]
Bye.

14:31.996 --> 14:34.540
[ Door opens, closes ]

14:38.044 --> 14:39.754
What did you put
on the medical forms?

14:39.754 --> 14:42.465
I...didn't put anything.

14:42.465 --> 14:43.883
What about
my antidepressants

14:43.883 --> 14:45.802
and the fact
that I see Dr. Heller?

14:45.802 --> 14:47.887
Did you leave that off?

14:47.887 --> 14:49.889
I did.

14:49.889 --> 14:53.184
Rome, there is such a stigma
around all this stuff.

14:53.184 --> 14:57.063
You remember what it did
to our life insurance premium.

14:57.063 --> 14:59.273
I just ‐‐ I didn't want it
to hurt our chances.

15:03.319 --> 15:06.280
No, look, I‐I'll run out
and stop her right now.

15:06.280 --> 15:08.199
I'll tell her
I need to adjust the form.

15:08.199 --> 15:10.701
N‐No, no, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait.

15:10.701 --> 15:11.994
You don't want me to?

15:13.621 --> 15:14.997
Honestly?

15:17.583 --> 15:19.377
I don't know.

15:19.377 --> 15:20.878
♪♪

15:24.132 --> 15:26.217
The thing is, Doc,
up until now,

15:26.217 --> 15:27.510
identifying as someone
suffering from depression

15:27.510 --> 15:28.719
was a box
that only <i>I</i> had to check,

15:28.719 --> 15:30.263
but with this adoption,

15:30.263 --> 15:32.014
checking that box
affects the both of us.

15:32.014 --> 15:33.808
And she's right ‐‐
there <i>is</i> a stigma.

15:33.808 --> 15:35.518
Rome, no one is saying

15:35.518 --> 15:37.979
that people successfully dealing
with mental health issues

15:37.979 --> 15:39.355
can't adopt.

15:39.355 --> 15:41.607
They don't have to say it.
It's how they feel.

15:41.607 --> 15:45.069
They look at people
with mental illness differently.

15:45.069 --> 15:47.613
That's why <i>I</i> didn't
seek help earlier.

15:47.613 --> 15:50.658
The way you and I
were raised, Doc,

15:50.658 --> 15:53.161
black men
weren't allowed to cry.

15:53.161 --> 15:54.620
We're taught to be tough

15:54.620 --> 15:57.665
because the world's gonna be
that much tougher on us.

15:57.665 --> 16:00.960
Never tell anyone
how you feel.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.045
The only person
you ask for help is Jesus.

16:03.045 --> 16:06.257
Stop me if I'm lying,
but that's how you survive.

16:06.257 --> 16:09.177
Until you have a handful
of pills in your mouth.

16:09.177 --> 16:12.597
Rome, you've been doing
so well.

16:12.597 --> 16:15.308
Why do you think
today threw you so much?

16:15.308 --> 16:16.559
I don't know.

16:16.559 --> 16:18.019
I mean...

16:21.689 --> 16:23.649
I always knew
what society thought.

16:23.649 --> 16:27.528
I just never realized
that Gina felt that way, too.

16:31.574 --> 16:34.076
Thanks for volunteering
to feed the cast.

16:34.076 --> 16:36.204
What can I say?
I'm a patron of the arts.

16:38.873 --> 16:40.291
Hey, Regina.

16:40.291 --> 16:41.542
Hi.

16:41.542 --> 16:42.919
Sophie ‐‐

16:42.919 --> 16:44.587
I'm gonna go
set the tables.

16:44.587 --> 16:46.005
No, wait a second.
Hey.

16:47.798 --> 16:49.759
You're really
not going tonight?

16:49.759 --> 16:51.344
I'll go tomorrow.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.137
Okay, fine.

16:53.137 --> 16:54.597
If you don't
show your brother

16:54.597 --> 16:56.349
the decency
of going to his opening,

16:56.349 --> 16:57.850
I'm taking away your car.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.645
So what?
I'm grounded anyway.

17:00.645 --> 17:03.439
And you didn't
give me the car.

17:03.439 --> 17:04.857
<i>Dad</i> wanted me to have it.

17:04.857 --> 17:11.280
♪♪

17:11.280 --> 17:13.115
I keep thinking
it's gonna get better,

17:13.115 --> 17:14.951
and it just keeps
getting worse.

17:17.995 --> 17:20.498
Well, you know how sometimes
grown‐ups make up stories

17:20.498 --> 17:24.043
to help explain things
that are hard to understand?

17:24.043 --> 17:26.003
You mean like what you guys did
with Charlie?

17:27.546 --> 17:28.756
[ Sighs ]

17:28.756 --> 17:30.258
Yes.

17:30.258 --> 17:31.926
You're getting older
now, T,

17:31.926 --> 17:34.554
and you can handle
knowing things.

17:34.554 --> 17:37.723
The reason why you haven't
met your Aunt Lindsay yet

17:37.723 --> 17:40.393
is because
she has a problem.

17:40.393 --> 17:42.019
What kind of problem?

17:42.019 --> 17:43.813
You know how...

17:43.813 --> 17:46.023
we were getting pizza
that one time

17:46.023 --> 17:48.526
and that guy
was <i>really</i> loud?

17:48.526 --> 17:50.486
Yeah, he was scary.

17:50.486 --> 17:51.737
You said he was drunk.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.281
Yeah, he was.

17:53.281 --> 17:56.909
Well, your Aunt Lindsay has
the same problem as that guy.

17:56.909 --> 17:59.036
She gets drunk a lot,

17:59.036 --> 18:01.789
and it's <i>really</i> bad
for her health.

18:01.789 --> 18:03.749
It's called
being an alcoholic.

18:05.585 --> 18:08.296
<i>That's</i> why she hasn't
come to visit us.

18:08.296 --> 18:10.756
It's just not a good idea
for us to be around her

18:10.756 --> 18:12.258
until she gets better.

18:12.258 --> 18:14.594
How can we help her
get better?

18:14.594 --> 18:17.138
Well, that's the thing ‐‐
you can't help someone

18:17.138 --> 18:19.015
until they want
to help themselves.

18:19.015 --> 18:21.976
Now, a lot of people
have this problem, and...

18:24.687 --> 18:26.522
...the truth is...

18:26.522 --> 18:36.490
♪♪

18:36.490 --> 18:38.075
...I have
the same problem.

18:40.369 --> 18:41.370
You do?

18:42.913 --> 18:45.541
Back when I was with the band,
I did a lot of stupid stuff.

18:45.541 --> 18:49.211
Is that why when Mom has
a glass of wine, you <i>don't?</i>

18:49.211 --> 18:50.379
Yes.

18:50.379 --> 18:53.132
And most people can drink,
and it's fine.

18:53.132 --> 18:54.967
But <i>I</i> can't.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.011
So I gave it up.

18:57.011 --> 18:58.387
It was hard.

18:58.387 --> 19:03.059
But not drinking made me
a better husband

19:03.059 --> 19:04.560
and made me
a better father.

19:04.560 --> 19:05.686
[ Chuckles ]

19:09.148 --> 19:10.941
It makes me
a better person.

19:10.941 --> 19:17.531
♪♪

19:17.531 --> 19:19.283
Then I'm really proud
of you, Dad.

19:19.283 --> 19:23.245
♪♪

19:23.245 --> 19:30.211
♪♪

19:30.211 --> 19:33.798
[ Indistinct talking ]

19:33.798 --> 19:35.132
Hi.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.260
You sure you don't want
to go tonight?

19:38.260 --> 19:40.096
You can come
with me and Rome.

19:43.933 --> 19:45.685
What do you say?

19:53.234 --> 19:55.277
The thing that has
impressed me the most

19:55.277 --> 19:58.239
since your dad passed

19:58.239 --> 20:00.199
is how you've been there
for Danny.

20:03.536 --> 20:05.329
Look, I <i>want</i>
to be there for him.

20:05.329 --> 20:06.872
Okay.

20:06.872 --> 20:08.332
So go.

20:08.332 --> 20:09.750
I mean, you don't even
have to talk ‐‐

20:09.750 --> 20:12.169
It's not about Mom.

20:12.169 --> 20:14.296
I see her every day.

20:14.296 --> 20:16.465
The person I don't want to see
is Eddie.

20:17.758 --> 20:19.427
Oh.

20:19.427 --> 20:22.513
I especially don't want to see
him and my mom there together.

20:22.513 --> 20:23.514
Soph ‐‐

20:23.514 --> 20:25.307
Look, everybody wants me
to get over it,

20:25.307 --> 20:26.892
but it's not that simple.

20:26.892 --> 20:33.190
♪♪

20:33.190 --> 20:35.151
[ Indistinct talking
in distance ]

20:39.655 --> 20:41.657
[ Knock on door ]

20:41.657 --> 20:42.950
Hey, Tera.

20:42.950 --> 20:45.494
It's "Tara."

20:45.494 --> 20:47.163
Well...

20:47.163 --> 20:49.498
in my defense, everyone
around here calls you Ms. Simon.

20:51.083 --> 20:53.210
It's, uh, "Simone."

20:53.210 --> 20:55.379
That was a test.
Congratulations. You passed.

20:55.379 --> 20:57.214
[ Chuckles ]

20:57.214 --> 20:58.340
You're back.

20:58.340 --> 21:00.384
Are you helping out
with the sets again?

21:00.384 --> 21:01.927
I am, indeed.

21:01.927 --> 21:04.305
Just threw the last coat
of paint on Grease Lightning.

21:04.305 --> 21:06.348
Kids are getting
into their costumes.

21:06.348 --> 21:08.017
Should be quite a night.

21:08.017 --> 21:10.269
Especially if
the paint doesn't dry.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.730
[ Chuckles ]

21:12.730 --> 21:16.108
I, uh, thought
you were gonna call me.

21:16.108 --> 21:17.777
My phone died.
Oh.

21:17.777 --> 21:19.612
I lost everything.
[ Clicks tongue ]

21:22.364 --> 21:23.657
[ Chuckles ]

21:26.744 --> 21:27.787
Danny.

21:27.787 --> 21:29.705
What?
Danny.

21:29.705 --> 21:31.540
Daniel Dixon.

21:31.540 --> 21:33.042
What's happening, man?

21:33.042 --> 21:36.086
If you'll excuse me,
I should...

21:36.086 --> 21:36.962
go.

21:40.674 --> 21:41.842
Break a leg, Danny.

21:43.803 --> 21:45.721
Hey, bud.
Everything okay?

21:45.721 --> 21:48.307
Actually, it's not.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.184
What were you doing
with her?

21:50.184 --> 21:52.019
Uncle Gary's trying
to get his grades up,

21:52.019 --> 21:54.605
so, uh...
he hired a tutor.

21:54.605 --> 21:57.858
You've been acting
so weird lately.

21:57.858 --> 21:59.693
Everyone thinks it ‐‐
not just me.

22:01.028 --> 22:03.155
It's like I don't even
recognize you anymore.

22:03.155 --> 22:04.657
What is that
supposed to mean?

22:04.657 --> 22:08.035
It means, why are you kissing
my Social Studies teacher?

22:08.035 --> 22:09.787
Because your Spanish teacher
is married.

22:09.787 --> 22:12.456
Hold on, Danny.
I'm sorry.

22:13.791 --> 22:15.084
It's just a kiss.

22:17.378 --> 22:19.463
Oh, is that
what this is about?

22:19.463 --> 22:21.841
Huh?

22:21.841 --> 22:23.968
You nervous about tonight?
About kissing Sandy?

22:23.968 --> 22:25.511
No.

22:25.511 --> 22:27.638
And I wish people would
stop asking me that.

22:29.765 --> 22:31.016
Is tonight
your first kiss?

22:33.435 --> 22:34.937
You're gonna do great.

22:34.937 --> 22:36.230
It's not a big deal.

22:36.230 --> 22:37.523
It <i>is</i> a big deal,

22:37.523 --> 22:40.693
and I wish it was
with someone I cared about.

22:40.693 --> 22:41.902
You mean Elliot.

22:41.902 --> 22:43.654
You wouldn't understand.

22:43.654 --> 22:46.240
Hey! This is me, okay?
Don't do that.

22:46.240 --> 22:50.119
What is wrong
with people?

22:50.119 --> 22:52.037
[ Voice breaking ] Why can't
they learn to stay together?

22:52.037 --> 22:53.497
Because it's hard, Danny.

22:53.497 --> 22:54.874
Maggie and I are not ‐‐

22:54.874 --> 22:56.166
I'm talking about
my parents!

22:58.419 --> 23:02.172
If they had stayed together,
none of this would've happened.

23:04.508 --> 23:06.260
Sophie's not even
coming tonight.

23:08.804 --> 23:10.180
[ Scoffs ]

23:10.180 --> 23:11.932
I'm sorry, pal.

23:11.932 --> 23:15.311
A kiss is
supposed to mean something.

23:15.311 --> 23:17.104
That's all I'm saying.

23:17.104 --> 23:22.067
♪♪

23:25.321 --> 23:27.656
Delilah: Hey, guys!
You made it!

23:27.656 --> 23:28.949
Did Sophie make it?

23:28.949 --> 23:30.826
Theo: Hi, Charlie.
Not yet. [ Chuckles ]

23:30.826 --> 23:32.828
Eddie: Well, if she ever talks
to us again, we can tell her

23:32.828 --> 23:34.622
I got a great deal
on that replacement guitar.

23:34.622 --> 23:36.415
It's gonna cost her
a lot less than we thought.

23:36.415 --> 23:38.709
Guitar?
You found the guitar?

23:38.709 --> 23:39.877
Yeah, I got
a great deal on it.

23:39.877 --> 23:40.878
Where?

23:40.878 --> 23:42.922
Uh...

23:42.922 --> 23:44.548
Eric found it for me.

23:44.548 --> 23:47.259
Eric "Steal your heart
and then your girl"...Eric?

23:47.259 --> 23:49.011
I didn't realize
he was back in the fold.

23:49.011 --> 23:50.346
They're just friends,
Gary.

23:52.848 --> 24:00.814
♪♪

24:00.814 --> 24:03.275
I'm gonna, um...

24:03.275 --> 24:05.945
get...

24:05.945 --> 24:07.321
s‐something to drink.

24:10.991 --> 24:12.034
Is there a bar?

24:14.912 --> 24:17.790
Uh, yeah.
My trip to Peru was great.

24:17.790 --> 24:20.793
Thanks for asking.

24:20.793 --> 24:22.503
Hi. Hey.

24:22.503 --> 24:25.464
Oh, I have your guitar
in my trunk, by the way.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.633
Think it's gonna cost us
a lot more than we thought.

24:29.426 --> 24:31.261
It really was.

24:31.261 --> 24:33.639
I caught him in the bathroom
practicing his dance moves.

24:33.639 --> 24:39.061
♪♪

24:39.061 --> 24:40.896
It's fun to be ignored,
isn't it?

24:40.896 --> 24:42.064
Super fun.

24:44.066 --> 24:45.442
See you in there?
Okay.

24:45.442 --> 24:47.277
Hey.

24:47.277 --> 24:48.570
Y'all know Gary's
right over there, right?

24:48.570 --> 24:50.364
Oh. He's right
over there?

24:50.364 --> 24:51.657
Huh.

24:51.657 --> 24:52.658
Thoug‐‐

24:52.658 --> 24:53.742
See you inside.

24:53.742 --> 24:54.868
Let's go.

24:54.868 --> 24:56.787
[ Laughs ]

24:56.787 --> 24:57.997
Hey, hey.
Yeah?

24:57.997 --> 24:59.665
Let me ask you something.

24:59.665 --> 25:01.542
Do you think
that my depression

25:01.542 --> 25:03.752
makes me less qualified
to be a father?

25:03.752 --> 25:05.713
No, of course not.

25:05.713 --> 25:07.172
I want this baby, Gina,
more than anything,

25:07.172 --> 25:08.424
but I can't ‐‐

25:08.424 --> 25:11.093
I can't have my first act
as a dad be a lie.

25:11.093 --> 25:19.309
♪♪

25:19.309 --> 25:20.978
[ Sighs ]

25:20.978 --> 25:22.896
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:25.441 --> 25:26.400
Hi.

25:26.400 --> 25:27.860
Yo.

25:27.860 --> 25:29.570
Think you're in my seat.

25:29.570 --> 25:31.405
Well...
switch seats with me?

25:31.405 --> 25:33.032
Then you'll be sitting here
by yourself.

25:33.032 --> 25:35.617
Yeah, and I'd prefer that
to sitting next to my mom.

25:35.617 --> 25:36.994
You know what?

25:36.994 --> 25:38.704
You two need
to work this out.

25:38.704 --> 25:40.706
Avoiding each other
is not the answer, Sophie.

25:41.665 --> 25:42.458
Fine.

25:47.129 --> 25:49.089
[ Whispering ]
Switch back. Switch back.

25:49.089 --> 25:50.215
[ Whispering ]
I don't want to.

25:50.215 --> 25:52.259
Maggie's over there.
I don't care.

25:52.259 --> 25:53.677
I don't care.

25:53.677 --> 25:55.721
[ Chuckles ]

25:55.721 --> 25:57.181
[ Clears throat ] Hi.

25:57.181 --> 25:57.890
Oh, hi!

25:57.890 --> 25:59.641
Hi, Charlie!

26:01.060 --> 26:02.269
Hi.

26:02.269 --> 26:03.645
[ Sighs ]

26:03.645 --> 26:05.355
Hello.

26:05.355 --> 26:07.441
[ Instruments tuning ]

26:12.237 --> 26:13.989
[ Whispering ]
Places. Places, everyone.

26:17.910 --> 26:19.703
[ Sighs heavily ]

26:24.500 --> 26:26.335
[ Charlie crying,
Delilah shushing ]

26:26.335 --> 26:28.170
[ "Hopelessly Devoted To You"
plays ]

26:28.170 --> 26:30.089
Uh, D, I can get her.

26:30.089 --> 26:31.799
It's okay.
[ Crying continues ]

26:31.799 --> 26:32.966
It's okay.

26:32.966 --> 26:34.635
Let me take her.

26:34.635 --> 26:36.053
You can't miss this.

26:36.053 --> 26:37.429
Thank you so much.

26:37.429 --> 26:38.597
It's okay.

26:38.597 --> 26:39.890
Let's go.

26:39.890 --> 26:41.183
Let's go.

26:41.183 --> 26:43.435
[ Crying continues ]

26:43.435 --> 26:49.733
♪ Guess mine is not
the first heart broken ♪

26:49.733 --> 26:56.657
♪ My eyes are not
the first to cry ♪

26:56.657 --> 26:59.785
♪ I'm not the first to know ♪

26:59.785 --> 27:03.914
♪ There's just
no getting over you ♪

27:03.914 --> 27:09.711
♪♪

27:09.711 --> 27:16.051
♪ I know I'm just a fool
who's willing ♪

27:16.051 --> 27:22.558
♪ To sit around
and wait for you ♪

27:22.558 --> 27:25.602
♪ But, baby, can't you see ♪

27:25.602 --> 27:30.232
♪ There's nothing left
for me to do ♪

27:32.192 --> 27:34.361
♪ I'm hopelessly devoted... ♪

27:34.361 --> 27:36.822
You really hurt
my feelings.

27:36.822 --> 27:38.156
What?

27:38.156 --> 27:41.326
All I did was like you.

27:41.326 --> 27:43.078
You barely talked to me
all rehearsal.

27:43.078 --> 27:45.205
♪ ...nowhere to hide ♪

27:45.205 --> 27:48.250
♪ Since you pushed my love
aside ♪

27:48.250 --> 27:52.212
♪ I'm out of my head ♪

27:52.212 --> 27:59.386
♪ Hopelessly devoted to you ♪

27:59.386 --> 28:03.724
I'm just so sick of people
hiding their feelings.

28:03.724 --> 28:06.810
I'm about to have my first kiss
with Skyler Burns,

28:06.810 --> 28:08.562
and I kinda wish
it was with ‐‐

28:08.562 --> 28:16.862
♪ Hopelessly devoted
to yooooooooo‐ou ♪

28:16.862 --> 28:20.282
[ Cheers and applause ]

28:20.282 --> 28:21.867
Hey, how was the first act?
Great.

28:21.867 --> 28:24.369
The sets look amazing.
Danny's killing it.

28:24.369 --> 28:26.788
You hear that, Charlie?
Your big brother's a star!

28:26.788 --> 28:28.957
Here goes nothing.

28:28.957 --> 28:30.876
Alright.
What do we got?

28:32.044 --> 28:35.213
Don't mind...if I do.

28:35.213 --> 28:36.173
[ Sighs ]

28:38.675 --> 28:40.093
How's the cupcake?

28:43.472 --> 28:44.765
[ Muffled ] Super dry.

28:44.765 --> 28:45.974
You got some...

28:45.974 --> 28:47.643
I was saving that
for later.

28:51.813 --> 28:54.358
Your hair looks good.

28:54.358 --> 28:56.360
If you were any shorter,
I'd think you were Charlie.

28:56.360 --> 28:57.319
[ Chuckles ]

28:59.613 --> 29:00.989
Well,
it's good to see you.

29:00.989 --> 29:02.783
I should probably walk away
from the baked goods.

29:02.783 --> 29:04.660
Gary. Hey, this is crazy. We
can't keep avoiding each other.

29:04.660 --> 29:06.036
Sure we can.

29:06.036 --> 29:07.454
Are you okay?
I'm fine.

29:07.454 --> 29:09.164
Are you sure?
'Cause you look tired.

29:09.164 --> 29:10.791
You been up all night
playing video games?

29:10.791 --> 29:13.126
Or up all night
with other distractions?

29:13.126 --> 29:14.878
You're biting your fingernails
again. Stop it.

29:14.878 --> 29:16.421
What are you,
an FBI profiler?

29:16.421 --> 29:18.548
I'm just worried
about you.

29:18.548 --> 29:20.175
What's up
with the dent in your car?

29:21.635 --> 29:22.928
I saw it when I came in.

29:22.928 --> 29:24.554
That wasn't even my fault.

29:24.554 --> 29:26.515
Look, you don't have to worry
about me, okay? I'm doing great.

29:26.515 --> 29:28.642
Spare me the "Make them
think you're doing better
than them" routine.

29:28.642 --> 29:30.060
I know you too well.

29:30.060 --> 29:31.144
You don't get
to have an opinion

29:31.144 --> 29:32.604
about how I live my life
anymore, Maggie.

29:32.604 --> 29:34.481
You lost that right
when you broke up with me.

29:34.481 --> 29:37.567
I'm sor‐‐
uh, <i>you</i> broke up with <i>me.</i>

29:37.567 --> 29:39.361
And how long did it take you
to call heart boy?

29:39.361 --> 29:40.487
Two days?

29:40.487 --> 29:42.030
Is that seriously
what this is about? I‐‐

29:42.030 --> 29:43.740
He is just a friend.
Keep telling yourself that.

29:43.740 --> 29:45.283
Alright,
you really want to know?

29:45.283 --> 29:46.994
Took me about five minutes
to call him,

29:46.994 --> 29:49.079
because he is the only person
I knew in town

29:49.079 --> 29:50.580
who wasn't
one of <i>your</i> friends.

29:50.580 --> 29:52.332
And at the time, I didn't
want to tell any of them,

29:52.332 --> 29:53.625
because, in that moment,

29:53.625 --> 29:56.044
I was hoping that you would
change your mind.

29:56.044 --> 29:59.256
♪♪

29:59.256 --> 30:01.174
Don't worry.
I don't feel that way now.

30:01.174 --> 30:03.844
Just ‐‐ enjoy your...
super‐dry cupcake.

30:03.844 --> 30:10.058
♪♪

30:14.104 --> 30:15.897
♪ When we go out at night ♪

30:15.897 --> 30:17.858
♪ And stars are shining bright ♪

30:17.858 --> 30:21.862
♪ Up in the skies above ♪

30:21.862 --> 30:23.947
♪ Or at the high school dance ♪

30:23.947 --> 30:25.824
♪ Where you can find romance ♪

30:25.824 --> 30:30.037
♪ Maybe it might be
lo‐o‐o‐o‐o‐o‐o‐ve ♪

30:30.037 --> 30:31.121
♪ We're for each other ♪

30:31.121 --> 30:32.622
Are we really
gonna do this?

30:32.622 --> 30:33.957
You mean kiss?
Yeah.

30:33.957 --> 30:35.751
In, like, five bars.

30:35.751 --> 30:37.753
I'm so nervous.

30:37.753 --> 30:39.171
I've done it before.

30:39.171 --> 30:40.672
It's gonna be totally fine.

30:40.672 --> 30:44.009
♪ We'll always be together ♪

30:44.009 --> 30:46.261
♪ Wha‐ooh, yeah! ♪

30:46.261 --> 30:50.098
♪ We'll always be together ♪

30:50.098 --> 30:54.478
♪ We'll always be together ♪

30:54.478 --> 30:58.857
[ Scatting ]
♪ We'll always be together ♪

30:58.857 --> 31:03.320
[ Scatting ]
♪ We'll always be together ♪

31:03.320 --> 31:07.574
[ Scatting ]
♪ We'll always be together ♪

31:07.574 --> 31:09.701
♪ A‐womp ba‐ba lu‐bop
a‐womp bam boom! ♪

31:09.701 --> 31:12.079
[ Cheers and applause ]

31:17.667 --> 31:18.960
[ Cheering continues ]

31:26.093 --> 31:28.678
[ Indistinct conversations,
laughter ]

31:31.973 --> 31:35.060
Oh, my God,
you were amazing!

31:35.060 --> 31:37.020
Thank you so much
for being here.

31:37.020 --> 31:38.188
I have news.
What?

31:38.188 --> 31:38.980
Big news.

31:40.565 --> 31:42.859
I'm so proud of you!

31:42.859 --> 31:44.528
Mwah! Come here.
Mwah!

31:44.528 --> 31:45.821
I'll see you at home.

31:48.198 --> 31:51.284
You seriously
killed it!

31:51.284 --> 31:53.161
And I wouldn't say it
if it wasn't true.

31:53.161 --> 31:55.288
And the kiss ‐‐
pretty awesome.

31:55.288 --> 31:56.748
Which one?

31:56.748 --> 31:58.959
What do you mean
"Which one"?

31:58.959 --> 32:00.836
Hey, Danny.
You coming to the cast party?

32:00.836 --> 32:02.087
Wouldn't miss it.

32:03.130 --> 32:04.589
Aww, dude.

32:04.589 --> 32:06.591
Danny. Really?

32:06.591 --> 32:07.592
Yeah.

32:07.592 --> 32:08.385
[ Chuckles ]

32:10.971 --> 32:12.973
You know...

32:12.973 --> 32:16.184
you were the first one
to know I was gay.

32:16.184 --> 32:18.562
Maybe even before <i>I</i> knew.

32:18.562 --> 32:20.355
You told me

32:20.355 --> 32:22.899
when I was ready
to tell you about Elliot,

32:22.899 --> 32:24.568
you were ready to listen.

32:24.568 --> 32:25.694
Remember?

32:25.694 --> 32:27.529
I do.

32:27.529 --> 32:30.157
Well, when <i>you're</i> ready
to tell me

32:30.157 --> 32:32.826
that you're still
in love with Maggie,

32:32.826 --> 32:34.077
I'm ready to hear it.

32:34.077 --> 32:39.207
♪♪

32:39.207 --> 32:40.625
Soph!

32:40.625 --> 32:41.835
Come on! Just ‐‐

32:41.835 --> 32:43.378
W‐Where are you going?

32:43.378 --> 32:44.880
Home.

32:44.880 --> 32:46.548
I did what you wanted.
I saw Danny in the play.

32:46.548 --> 32:47.966
Oh, God,
I can't take it anymore!

32:47.966 --> 32:49.134
Can we please
just talk?

32:49.134 --> 32:51.428
[ Sighs ] No.

32:51.428 --> 32:52.762
You keep wanting to talk,

32:52.762 --> 32:54.264
but nothing you say
changes anything.

32:55.432 --> 32:56.725
Delilah?

32:58.518 --> 33:01.563
See? This. This is exactly why
I didn't want to come tonight ‐‐

33:01.563 --> 33:05.108
to see you two with Charlie,
acting like nothing's wrong!

33:05.108 --> 33:07.611
[ Sighs ] How could you
do that to him?

33:07.611 --> 33:09.779
To your husband?
To your best friend?

33:09.779 --> 33:11.698
Delilah: Okay, you know what?
That's enough. Stop!

33:11.698 --> 33:13.658
That's enough!

33:13.658 --> 33:15.952
I know what I did.
I know it was wrong.

33:15.952 --> 33:17.746
But I did not
kill your father.

33:17.746 --> 33:21.124
He took his own life for reasons
that are more complicated

33:21.124 --> 33:24.377
than we will
ever understand.

33:24.377 --> 33:26.463
And you can hate me.
You can hate me all you want.

33:26.463 --> 33:28.798
But I will not let you
blame me for that.

33:28.798 --> 33:31.301
[ Voice breaking ]
You ruined everything!

33:31.301 --> 33:33.178
Okay, let's just go home.
Please ‐‐

33:33.178 --> 33:34.971
No, no.
Don't touch me.

33:34.971 --> 33:38.308
I'm not going home.

33:38.308 --> 33:41.645
I don't even want
to live with you anymore.

33:41.645 --> 33:43.647
[ Delilah sighs ]

33:43.647 --> 33:45.899
♪♪

33:49.611 --> 33:54.449
♪♪

33:54.449 --> 33:56.826
Rome?

33:56.826 --> 33:58.912
I want to explain
earlier.

33:58.912 --> 34:00.163
You don't need to.

34:02.082 --> 34:03.500
No, I <i>do.</i>

34:05.252 --> 34:07.295
You've been through
a lot.

34:07.295 --> 34:09.172
Last year...

34:09.172 --> 34:13.260
when I found your note,
it...threw me.

34:13.260 --> 34:15.595
I didn't know
you were depressed,

34:15.595 --> 34:18.306
much less suicidal.

34:18.306 --> 34:20.642
So, when you tell me
you're in a better place now,

34:20.642 --> 34:22.644
I believe you.

34:22.644 --> 34:25.188
But sometimes I wonder
how long that will last.

34:26.606 --> 34:28.149
Me too.

34:30.944 --> 34:34.572
And if it does come back,

34:34.572 --> 34:37.158
will I be able
to recognize it this time?

34:38.952 --> 34:41.329
So, if you're asking
if sometimes I still worry,

34:41.329 --> 34:43.164
yes, I do.

34:43.164 --> 34:45.792
But everything you've done
to get help ‐‐

34:45.792 --> 34:49.129
seeing Dr. Heller,
getting on the meds ‐‐

34:49.129 --> 34:50.964
that is all stuff
you should be proud of.

34:50.964 --> 34:52.799
It's stuff <i>I'm</i> proud of.

34:52.799 --> 34:54.551
Because all of it
is a testament

34:54.551 --> 34:57.137
to how ready you are
to be a father.

34:57.137 --> 34:59.723
♪♪

34:59.723 --> 35:03.059
I revised
our medical history.

35:03.059 --> 35:05.061
I'm sorry.

35:05.061 --> 35:07.105
Any birth mother
who reads our application

35:07.105 --> 35:10.025
will know what a great parent
you're gonna be.

35:11.776 --> 35:12.736
<i>We're</i> gonna be.

35:12.736 --> 35:14.487
[ Clatter ]

35:14.487 --> 35:16.906
Sophie?
Sophie: Sorry!

35:16.906 --> 35:18.783
You wanted a kid,
we got a kid.

35:18.783 --> 35:20.744
I just hope we're not
on the hook for college.

35:20.744 --> 35:22.412
[ Chuckles ]

35:22.412 --> 35:24.122
There she is.

35:25.498 --> 35:28.043
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

35:28.043 --> 35:29.419
Regina: Hi.

35:29.419 --> 35:31.254
[ Sighing ] Uh...
no, it's okay.

35:31.254 --> 35:32.672
No, she's just
getting settled.

35:32.672 --> 35:35.216
Are you sure
this is the right thing to do?

35:35.216 --> 35:36.676
We have to try.

35:36.676 --> 35:38.470
Maggie said
it was a good idea.

35:38.470 --> 35:40.138
Just...

35:40.138 --> 35:41.640
I feel like I failed her.

35:41.640 --> 35:43.224
No!

35:43.224 --> 35:45.185
No, you're letting us
help you.

35:45.185 --> 35:46.394
We're family, D.

35:46.394 --> 35:47.937
[ Sniffles ]

35:47.937 --> 35:49.272
Just take care of her.

35:49.272 --> 35:50.940
We will.

35:50.940 --> 35:54.027
And then we'll send her home,
where she belongs.

35:54.027 --> 35:55.695
Thank you.
[ Chuckles softly ]

35:55.695 --> 35:58.239
[ Sighs ]

35:58.239 --> 35:59.407
[ Cellphone beeps ]
[ Sniffles ]

35:59.407 --> 36:00.867
♪♪

36:00.867 --> 36:01.951
[ Knock on door ]

36:04.204 --> 36:05.205
Hey.

36:05.205 --> 36:07.457
How was the cast party?

36:07.457 --> 36:08.667
Really fun.

36:08.667 --> 36:10.043
We had beer.

36:11.836 --> 36:13.088
[ Chuckling ] Root beer.

36:13.088 --> 36:14.172
[ Chuckles ]

36:14.172 --> 36:16.633
See what I did?
[ Sighs ]

36:16.633 --> 36:17.842
[ Chuckles ]

36:19.844 --> 36:21.805
I had my first kiss
tonight.

36:21.805 --> 36:23.598
I know. I saw.

36:23.598 --> 36:25.058
No, you didn't.

36:25.058 --> 36:27.102
That was my <i>second</i> one.

36:27.102 --> 36:28.561
I kissed Elliot.

36:28.561 --> 36:29.771
[ Laughs ]

36:29.771 --> 36:31.564
Well, technically,
<i>he</i> kissed <i>me.</i>

36:31.564 --> 36:32.941
He did?

36:32.941 --> 36:34.526
[ Laughing ] Oh!

36:34.526 --> 36:35.652
So, are you guys ‐‐

36:35.652 --> 36:37.821
No, Mom. No labels.

36:37.821 --> 36:39.823
Don't say anything.

36:39.823 --> 36:41.574
It is what it is.

36:41.574 --> 36:44.577
What it is,
is pretty fantastic.

36:44.577 --> 36:45.453
Yeah.

36:45.453 --> 36:46.788
[ Chuckles ]

36:46.788 --> 36:49.582
It <i>is</i> pretty great.

36:49.582 --> 36:51.376
[ Chuckles ]

36:51.376 --> 36:55.547
♪♪

36:55.547 --> 36:59.426
All that stuff going on
with Sophie...

36:59.426 --> 37:01.803
She was so upset
to be at that show tonight.

37:01.803 --> 37:04.514
At least
she was there for Danny.

37:04.514 --> 37:06.099
Yeah.

37:06.099 --> 37:07.559
She was there
for her brother.

37:10.520 --> 37:12.814
I think I want
to reach out to Lindsay.

37:12.814 --> 37:15.358
Are you sure
that's a good idea, Eddie?

37:15.358 --> 37:17.068
I mean,
you said it yourself.

37:17.068 --> 37:19.112
You can't help someone who
doesn't want to help themselves.

37:19.112 --> 37:21.781
And I know, but the card,
those gifts for Charlie ‐‐

37:21.781 --> 37:22.866
she's reaching out.

37:22.866 --> 37:24.492
I don't know.

37:24.492 --> 37:27.412
Something about it
just feels different this time.

37:27.412 --> 37:28.747
How can I ignore that?

37:32.667 --> 37:34.794
What are you
still doing up, T?

37:34.794 --> 37:36.463
I couldn't fall asleep.

37:36.463 --> 37:39.591
I was just wondering...

37:39.591 --> 37:41.509
could it come back?

37:41.509 --> 37:43.178
What?

37:43.178 --> 37:44.345
Your problem.

37:45.680 --> 37:49.017
♪♪

37:49.017 --> 37:51.227
Oh. Hey, bud.
Come here.

37:51.227 --> 37:56.441
♪♪

37:56.441 --> 37:59.152
This is
a part of me.

37:59.152 --> 38:01.029
It will always be
a part of me.

38:01.029 --> 38:03.948
But...

38:03.948 --> 38:08.328
the difference is,
I now admit it's a problem.

38:08.328 --> 38:10.705
And...

38:10.705 --> 38:13.666
I have you...

38:13.666 --> 38:15.001
and Mom...

38:15.001 --> 38:16.711
who believe in me.

38:16.711 --> 38:20.298
As long as I have that,
there's nothing I can't do.

38:20.298 --> 38:22.884
♪♪

38:22.884 --> 38:25.345
Well, you can't fly.

38:25.345 --> 38:26.554
Oh.

38:26.554 --> 38:29.015
Didn't I tell you?

38:29.015 --> 38:30.266
[ Whispering ]
I'm actually Superman.

38:30.266 --> 38:31.851
Do <i>not</i> tell your mother.

38:31.851 --> 38:33.686
[ Laughs ]
Okay?

38:33.686 --> 38:36.105
[ Laughter ]

38:36.105 --> 38:37.732
[ Crickets chirping ]

38:37.732 --> 38:40.527
[ Inhales deeply ]

38:40.527 --> 38:41.903
Alright.

38:41.903 --> 38:43.321
[ Inhales sharply ]

38:45.657 --> 38:47.116
What the...?

38:49.494 --> 38:51.204
[ Vehicle approaches ]

38:52.789 --> 38:54.374
Hey! Hey!!

38:54.374 --> 38:55.959
You see that sign?!

38:55.959 --> 38:57.961
[ Tires screech ]
It says "Stop," bro!

38:59.712 --> 39:01.047
Oh, you're getting out?

39:01.047 --> 39:02.841
[ Chuckling ] Oh!
He's a big boy.

39:02.841 --> 39:04.133
What you gonna ‐‐

39:04.133 --> 39:10.431
♪♪

39:10.431 --> 39:16.771
♪♪

39:16.771 --> 39:17.981
[ Breathing shakily ]

39:17.981 --> 39:19.816
[ Car door closes ]

39:19.816 --> 39:21.568
[ Tires squeal, engine revs ]

39:21.568 --> 39:27.740
♪♪

39:27.740 --> 39:29.200
[ Exhales deeply ]

39:29.200 --> 39:30.285
What'd I tell you?

39:30.285 --> 39:32.495
Running it out
did the trick, right?

39:32.495 --> 39:33.663
[ Panting ]
Didn't work.

39:33.663 --> 39:35.540
Still annoyed.

39:35.540 --> 39:36.791
You know, I just ‐‐

39:36.791 --> 39:39.127
I cannot believe
what an ass Gary was.

39:39.127 --> 39:41.588
Well, breaking up
is hard to do.

39:41.588 --> 39:42.672
Isn't that from "Grease"?

39:42.672 --> 39:44.591
That is Neil Sedaka.

39:44.591 --> 39:46.801
You run a music store.
You should definitely know that.

39:46.801 --> 39:48.428
[ Laughing ] People are
gonna think you're a fraud.

39:48.428 --> 39:50.305
[ Chuckles ]

39:50.305 --> 39:52.307
I will work on that.
[ Laughs ]

39:52.307 --> 39:56.394
It was Chloe
who loved music and musicals.

39:56.394 --> 39:59.105
Every year for Halloween,
she dressed up as someone,

39:59.105 --> 40:00.440
like Annie.
Mm.

40:00.440 --> 40:01.816
And made me
dress up, too.

40:01.816 --> 40:04.652
You shoulda seen me
in a bald wig.

40:04.652 --> 40:06.446
[ Chuckles ] I'll bet
you looked even better than me.

40:06.446 --> 40:08.698
[ Laughs ] Yeah.

40:08.698 --> 40:09.490
Whew! [ Sighs ]

40:09.490 --> 40:14.662
♪♪

40:14.662 --> 40:16.122
Oh, don't worry.

40:16.122 --> 40:18.666
I‐I didn't...
see your scar.

40:18.666 --> 40:20.001
[ Chuckles ]

40:20.001 --> 40:21.502
I‐I get it.

40:21.502 --> 40:24.130
I'm...

40:24.130 --> 40:26.925
super self‐conscious
about mine, too.

40:29.052 --> 40:31.721
It's half the reason
I'm afraid to date again.

40:31.721 --> 40:38.186
♪♪

40:38.186 --> 40:40.647
What do you do
when you're with someone?

40:40.647 --> 40:43.149
I, uh...

40:47.445 --> 40:50.698
No, I, um...

40:50.698 --> 40:54.243
I mean, I‐I haven't
been with anyone since...

40:54.243 --> 40:55.828
Chloe.

40:55.828 --> 41:05.588
♪♪

41:05.588 --> 41:14.973
♪♪

41:14.973 --> 41:24.732
♪♪

41:24.732 --> 41:25.900
I'm s‐‐ I'm sorry.

41:25.900 --> 41:27.360
No, um...
I just ‐‐

41:27.360 --> 41:28.820
I‐I know ‐‐ I thought ‐‐
I'm sorry.

41:28.820 --> 41:29.946
